
   MEng / PhD Research Proposal
   Department of Electrical, Electronic and Computer Engineering

NOTE: This template is for students who HAVE completed EIN732.
      Students who have not completed EIN732 must use the alternative
      template available on the departmental website.

Prospective MEng and PhD students must submit a document in which the
proposed research is explained. The proposal document must adhere to
specific formatting guidelines otherwise the proposal will not be
considered.  This package includes a LaTeX class file and template
document which will allow a research proposal to be generated based on
the required format.

The template requires a standard LaTeX installation such as MiTeX
under Windows, or TexLive under Linux. In the case of MiTeX additional
packages will need to be installed and this should happen
automatically. The additional packages are: fancyhdr and titlesec.

To create a research proposal using this template, edit the main file
research_proposal.tex. The title page of the research proposal is
created automatically based on macros at the top of the
research_proposal.tex file.  These macros must be updated
appropriately. Note that the "\rptype" macro must be either "MEng" or
"PhD" and the study leader designation will be automatically be
updated. The bulk of the research proposal content should be entered
in the "content.tex" file. The file already contains all the required
headings / sections and these should not be altered.

A standard Makefile is included that will generate the output PDF
file. A Windows TeXnicCenter project file is also included.

NOTE: Remember to attach the EIN732 research proposal (final assignment)
      to this research proposal as part of the submission.
